1
00:00:04,130 --> 00:00:06,930
Encounter

2
00:00:13,900 --> 00:00:16,200
Song Hye Kyo

3
00:00:24,610 --> 00:00:26,680
Park Bo Gum

4
00:00:33,140 --> 00:00:36,900
Boyfriend

5
00:00:52,280 --> 00:00:54,190
The CEO came.

6
00:00:54,190 --> 00:00:56,720
You should escort her inside. What are you guys doing just standing there?

7
00:00:56,720 --> 00:00:58,460
Come on in.

8
00:00:58,460 --> 00:01:00,000
Yes. Come in.

9
00:01:00,060 --> 00:01:03,570
Thank you for inviting me and allowing me to come to your place.

10
00:01:03,570 --> 00:01:07,150
We're just having a meal together. It's not such a big deal.

11
00:01:07,150 --> 00:01:09,760
I wasn't sure what to bring.

12
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:15,320
Oh. You could have just come. I didn't prepare a lot of food.

13
00:01:16,370 --> 00:01:17,830
Come this way.

14
00:01:17,830 --> 00:01:19,390
Yes.

15
00:01:22,660 --> 00:01:26,510
Rice. Rice. Rice.

16
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:36,450
Episode 13

17
00:01:46,620 --> 00:01:49,610
CEO Cha's car has arrived.

18
00:01:50,470 --> 00:01:51,970
- CEO Cha So Hyeon!
- CEO Cha So Hyeon!

19
00:01:51,970 --> 00:01:54,300
- Please look here.
- CEO, CEO Cha Soo Hyeon!

20
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:57,170
- Here she comes! Here she comes!
- CEO Cha! CEO! CEO Cha!

21
00:01:57,200 --> 00:02:00,110
This way, CEO! CEO Cha! Please look this way!

22
00:02:00,110 --> 00:02:01,890
Please raise your head!

23
00:02:01,890 --> 00:02:04,050
- What?
- What is this?

24
00:02:04,050 --> 00:02:06,700
CEO Cha had a conflicting scheduled appointment. She will not be able to attend.

25
00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:09,600
I came to announce this personally.

26
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:12,800
Yes. I understand. I will inform them.

27
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:15,000
Yes. Then.

28
00:02:25,300 --> 00:02:30,490
This is the taste! I have to learn how to make kimchi from Jin Hyeok's mom.

29
00:02:31,370 --> 00:02:34,220
- Isn't it delicious, CEO?
- Yes.

30
00:02:34,220 --> 00:02:36,560
It's very delicious, Mother.
(Employing the term a fiancée uses to refer to her mother-in-law)

31
00:02:36,570 --> 00:02:41,490
Ah! Wh-What a relief! E-Eat a lot.
(Using honorific term)

32
00:02:41,490 --> 00:02:43,450
Please speak comfortably.

33
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:47,800
If we're going to speak comfortably, then let's have yaja-time.
(A game where honorifics are reversed from oldest to youngest)

34
00:02:47,800 --> 00:02:49,700
So we can get close really quickly.

35
00:02:49,700 --> 00:02:52,400
- Just eat.
- Okay.

36
00:02:53,980 --> 00:02:58,380
We're going to have a problem. I think I will eat two bowls of rice today.

37
00:02:58,400 --> 00:03:03,400
Mmm. This. This. Did you also make this pickled plum?

38
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:07,000
Yes. That there. Even though it's for spring,

39
00:03:07,000 --> 00:03:10,000
I heard it retains its flavor for a long time.

40
00:03:10,060 --> 00:03:14,140
Ah! You prepare this kind of dish too. You are so cool.

41
00:03:14,180 --> 00:03:16,500
Ah! No.

42
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:19,600
My mom is good at preparing fruit dishes.

43
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:23,250
She's just halfway taking care of fruits that are almost spoiled.

44
00:03:23,250 --> 00:03:25,350
Is Dae Chan's store not getting much business? You've already eaten everything.

45
00:03:25,350 --> 00:03:28,870
His store isn't getting much business, and I'm going to eat even more.

46
00:03:29,900 --> 00:03:31,300
Eat a lot.

47
00:03:31,300 --> 00:03:34,800
Dad, why are you so quiet? Are you holding back?

48
00:03:35,990 --> 00:03:38,600
I'm not.

49
00:03:38,600 --> 00:03:40,500
Aigoo. This guy.

50
00:03:41,700 --> 00:03:43,700
Eat a lot.

51
00:03:43,700 --> 00:03:45,900
- Enjoy your meal.
- Yes.

52
00:03:45,930 --> 00:03:48,860
The short ribs are delicious.

53
00:03:59,250 --> 00:04:01,990
It's like this everyday, isn't it?

54
00:04:01,990 --> 00:04:07,450
At your house, it's like this everyday, lively and comfortable. Right?

55
00:04:07,450 --> 00:04:12,840
Ey! Sometimes, when my parents argue, it's like a war.

56
00:04:13,710 --> 00:04:16,590
I don't think so.

57
00:04:18,290 --> 00:04:20,570
Jin Hyeok.

58
00:04:21,460 --> 00:04:26,960
You thought I might have a hard time. That's why you told me the dinner was cancelled, right?

59
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:34,200
If it were me, I think I would have told you to stop going to Taegyeong Group's events.

60
00:04:34,200 --> 00:04:37,100
I don't think I would have been able to be so considerate.

61
00:04:37,100 --> 00:04:42,700
Actually, I know this situation makes you feel uneasy.

62
00:04:45,800 --> 00:04:52,170
As for me, wherever Soo Hyeon goes or whoever she has to meet

63
00:04:52,170 --> 00:04:54,880
doesn't make me uncomfortable.

64
00:04:54,900 --> 00:05:00,400
Soo Hyeon, all of the time that you've lived until now is meaningful

65
00:05:00,400 --> 00:05:03,600
and has a purpose.

66
00:05:03,630 --> 00:05:08,840
No matter where you go or what you do, your heart will come back to me.

67
00:05:10,960 --> 00:05:12,890
Right?

68
00:05:22,490 --> 00:05:24,980
- I was a bit awkward, right?
- Huh?

69
00:05:24,980 --> 00:05:27,950
Did I make your parents uncomfortable?

70
00:05:27,950 --> 00:05:31,880
I guess you don't know what uncomfortable feels like.

71
00:05:31,880 --> 00:05:33,580
You all got along well together.

72
00:05:33,620 --> 00:05:35,170
I was actually quite surprised.

73
00:05:35,170 --> 00:05:36,660
Really?

74
00:05:36,700 --> 00:05:40,450
"Wow. You make this kind of dish too?"

75
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:43,200
- Stop.
- "It's very delicious, Mother."

76
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:46,400
- Stop! When did I say that?
- "You are so cool."

77
00:05:46,400 --> 00:05:47,900
Stop!

78
00:05:47,900 --> 00:05:49,200
"Stop!"

79
00:05:49,210 --> 00:05:50,850
- Oh! Stop it.
- "Oh!"

80
00:05:50,900 --> 00:05:52,300
"Stop it."

81
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:11,650
Go get some rest.

82
00:06:11,650 --> 00:06:14,310
Your father

83
00:06:15,170 --> 00:06:17,860
must be upset.

84
00:06:30,210 --> 00:06:32,690
Oh! Hey. Hey. Hey.

85
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:35,300
Eat some rice and drink some water with it.
(The dish is too spicy.)

86
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:37,600
I won't be satisfied with those, okay?

87
00:06:37,640 --> 00:06:39,330
It's been so long since I've had homemade food like this.

88
00:06:39,330 --> 00:06:41,370
Slowly. Slowly.

89
00:06:41,410 --> 00:06:43,500
You're here.

90
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:45,240
Did you take the CEO back safely?

91
00:06:45,240 --> 00:06:47,900
- Of course, I did.
- Hey.

92
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:51,600
Now that she's met your parents, you two are going full steam ahead?

93
00:06:51,660 --> 00:06:54,530
Kim Jin Hyeok was smiling from ear to ear. Do you like her that much?

94
00:06:54,530 --> 00:06:56,240
Yes, I like her that much.

95
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:58,970
Oh. It's too spicy. I'm going to go get something to drink.

96
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:01,600
That's why I told you to eat it with rice and drink something.

97
00:07:01,600 --> 00:07:04,300
I felt that way. About my sister-in-law.

98
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:05,900
Hey. Yah!

99
00:07:05,900 --> 00:07:07,900
I mean, CEO.

100
00:07:07,900 --> 00:07:12,900
I was a little worried about having the CEO over at our place.

101
00:07:12,900 --> 00:07:14,110
Is that so?

102
00:07:14,110 --> 00:07:19,800
But when she came and was with our family, I was watching, like, "This looks good."

103
00:07:21,590 --> 00:07:24,300
If Mom and Dad think like that, it'd be good.

104
00:07:24,300 --> 00:07:28,220
Of course. You just worry about your relationship, Hyung.

105
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:29,650
Still, I'm worried.

106
00:07:29,650 --> 00:07:31,250
About what?

107
00:07:31,250 --> 00:07:34,400
Dad came to visit me at the company one time.

108
00:07:34,400 --> 00:07:35,610
What did he say?

109
00:07:35,610 --> 00:07:38,140
He was asking me if we would be okay.

110
00:07:38,170 --> 00:07:39,620
I asked him to trust us.

111
00:07:39,620 --> 00:07:41,460
That's good.

112
00:07:41,460 --> 00:07:43,420
How about Mom?

113
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:47,340
Ah ... As for Mom ... I'm not sure.

114
00:07:47,400 --> 00:07:49,800
I think Mom was really surprised today.

115
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:53,400
You know, it was kind of like... the calm before a storm, maybe?

116
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:56,700
So, I'm kind of scared to ask her anything about it.

117
00:07:56,700 --> 00:07:58,040
Should I ask her for you?

118
00:07:58,040 --> 00:08:01,750
No, that's okay. I should just talk to her tomorrow.

119
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:04,680
How about you?

120
00:08:04,680 --> 00:08:05,640
What?

121
00:08:05,640 --> 00:08:08,000
Your friends don't bother you about it?

122
00:08:08,000 --> 00:08:12,480
Aigoo. If I cared about stuff like that, I wouldn't be able to survive.

123
00:08:12,480 --> 00:08:16,400
You like her. Why are you only worrying about the people around you so much?

124
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:20,190
So when are you two getting married?

125
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:22,950
Really! How can I discuss anything with you?

126
00:08:22,950 --> 00:08:26,090
Why? You date, then bam! You just register your marriage and it's done.

127
00:08:26,090 --> 00:08:29,110
Jin Hyeok! Hey! You're going to register your marriage first?
(Registration before the ceremony implies the girlfriend is pregnant)

128
00:08:29,110 --> 00:08:32,080
Hey, yo— You guys go well together! Totally!

129
00:08:32,080 --> 00:08:34,230
Good luck, Chan's Whelks!

130
00:08:34,230 --> 00:08:37,140
Aigoo, how long has it been since I had homemade food?

131
00:08:37,140 --> 00:08:39,120
- It's hot!
- Let's eat it together.

132
00:08:39,200 --> 00:08:41,900
- My mom's kimchi stew is really delicious.
- Ah, it's delicious. So good!

133
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:34,300
After I went and begged like that—

134
00:09:34,300 --> 00:09:35,600
Look at the article.

135
00:09:35,600 --> 00:09:40,500
They're going crazy saying something like the long relationship between Taegyeong Group and Assemblyman Cha Jong Hyeon has ended.

136
00:09:40,500 --> 00:09:42,500
Ah. Sit down. Let's eat breakfast.

137
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:45,160
That's all old news. Why are you like this?

138
00:09:45,160 --> 00:09:48,390
Honey, you eat a lot.

139
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:03,370
You were really upset, weren't you?

140
00:10:04,270 --> 00:10:08,510
No. I fully understand your position.

141
00:10:08,600 --> 00:10:11,000
Thank you.

142
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:16,700
I asked to see you because you'll be holding a meeting for Cha Soo Hyeon's reappointment as CEO soon. Isn't that right?

143
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:18,380
Yes. That's true.

144
00:10:18,380 --> 00:10:20,130
Influence the directors.

145
00:10:20,130 --> 00:10:26,880
Use this opportunity to move Cha Soo Hyeon from her position and make CEO Jeong Woo Seok the sole CEO.

146
00:10:28,190 --> 00:10:35,220
Ah... If I'm to do that, I need a guarantee that the power of our directors will be enough to win for certain.

147
00:10:35,220 --> 00:10:40,670
It's already been taken care of. You just have to hold the Board of Directors meeting.

148
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:44,190
Yes. I will proceed as you have directed.

149
00:10:56,570 --> 00:10:58,870
Legal Team.

150
00:10:58,870 --> 00:11:03,560
Begin the case on getting Donghwa Hotel right away.

151
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:10,100
Assemblyman Cha Jeong Hyeon is no longer our concern.

152
00:11:10,100 --> 00:11:15,090
Make sure you take Donghwa Hotel.

153
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:27,330
There were a few of the same model, but it took time to find one made in the same year.

154
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:30,940
You worked hard. Thank you.

155
00:11:32,330 --> 00:11:36,060
By the way, do you think Assemblyman Cha will be all right?

156
00:11:36,060 --> 00:11:38,720
I feel like Taegyeong is going to make both of your lives difficult.

157
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:43,810
They'll push forward with the lawsuit to take Donghwa Hotel again, won't they?

158
00:11:43,810 --> 00:11:48,270
That's what those people live for. Don't worry about it.

159
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:49,640
Yes.

160
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:18,480
Will the ad for the hotel wedding discount be going out in print, too?

161
00:12:18,480 --> 00:12:22,390
It's been decided that it will be publicized in Donghwa's second quarter issue and only two luxury brand magazines.

162
00:12:22,390 --> 00:12:26,830
Let's take some good pictures. We have to make sure people are dying to get married at Donghwa Hotel.

163
00:12:26,830 --> 00:12:27,920
Yes, Department Head.

164
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:30,830
Also, how many wedding planners have we pared it down to?

165
00:12:30,830 --> 00:12:34,030
Going by your criteria, we've narrowed it down to three.

166
00:12:34,030 --> 00:12:37,880
Among those, let's go with the one that has the most experience in doing hotel weddings.

167
00:12:37,880 --> 00:12:38,980
Yes.

168
00:12:38,980 --> 00:12:43,650
When spring comes, the waves of weddings will overflow.

169
00:12:43,650 --> 00:12:46,430
And my pockets will soon be emptied, too.
(because of wedding gift money)

170
00:12:46,430 --> 00:12:48,500
Do you go to all of your friends' weddings?

171
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:53,160
You never know. If none of them comes to my wedding, it'll make me look as if I'm not a nice person.

172
00:12:53,160 --> 00:12:55,710
I'm thinking of it as an exchange of labor.

173
00:12:56,450 --> 00:13:00,930
Oh, who was the one in charge of the model agency last time?

174
00:13:00,930 --> 00:13:02,630
Section Chief Lee.

175
00:13:04,690 --> 00:13:06,430
Section Chief Lee?

176
00:13:09,030 --> 00:13:09,860
Yes.

177
00:13:09,860 --> 00:13:14,760
The model agency ... No, let's have Assistant Manager Park take it over.

178
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:18,110
You seem a little tired these days, and we can't risk something going wrong.

179
00:13:18,110 --> 00:13:21,440
No, I'll keep doing it.

180
00:13:21,440 --> 00:13:23,690
- Are you sure?
- Yes.

181
00:13:23,690 --> 00:13:28,510
Fine. Then let's decide on the concept after discussing it with the photographer and the wedding planner.

182
00:13:28,510 --> 00:13:29,930
Yes.

183
00:13:30,950 --> 00:13:33,550
I think the wedding planner is the one that's from...

184
00:14:03,800 --> 00:14:06,710
Dad, I caused trouble.

185
00:14:06,710 --> 00:14:09,110
What do I do? I feel sorry towards you.

186
00:14:09,110 --> 00:14:11,530
You did well.

187
00:14:11,530 --> 00:14:14,280
Seeing how you've been acting these days, I'm learning from you.

188
00:14:14,280 --> 00:14:17,280
Your election is coming soon, though.

189
00:14:17,280 --> 00:14:21,400
Soo Yeon, I've been holding back

190
00:14:21,400 --> 00:14:25,500
since it's too early to explain things in a way that would bring some relief.

191
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:31,950
But don't be shocked at how I behave as a politician from now on,

192
00:14:31,950 --> 00:14:36,220
and don't ever have strange thoughts like it might be because of you.

193
00:14:36,220 --> 00:14:39,450
What do you mean?

194
00:14:39,450 --> 00:14:42,600
I'm saying let us live properly.

195
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:45,420
You live your life happily,

196
00:14:45,420 --> 00:14:49,340
and I will live properly as me.

197
00:15:57,140 --> 00:15:59,560
Is the camera broken?

198
00:15:59,560 --> 00:16:02,620
This one is from Jeonjoo.

199
00:16:02,620 --> 00:16:04,560
Huh? Jeonjoo?

200
00:16:04,560 --> 00:16:09,630
It was hard to find one that was made in the same year as the one you gave me.

201
00:16:09,630 --> 00:16:11,820
Did you know it's the same model?

202
00:16:11,820 --> 00:16:14,090
I feel a little proud of myself.

203
00:16:14,090 --> 00:16:16,540
Seriously. What are you saying?

204
00:16:16,540 --> 00:16:19,340
The only way to tell is for the expert to take a look. Stay right there.

205
00:16:19,340 --> 00:16:20,810
I'll come over and look at it myself.

206
00:16:20,810 --> 00:16:22,740
I'll show it to you at work tomorrow.

207
00:16:22,740 --> 00:16:24,810
This is the worst.

208
00:16:24,810 --> 00:16:27,190
If your dad showed you a present he bought you

209
00:16:27,190 --> 00:16:31,800
but said, "Only look at it. Play with it tomorrow," how can you sleep?

210
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:35,500
I didn't say anything about giving it to you.

211
00:16:37,570 --> 00:16:39,230
Ah.

212
00:16:40,030 --> 00:16:43,750
What are you going to do with two of the same cameras?

213
00:16:43,750 --> 00:16:45,710
Why do you keep making fun of me?

214
00:16:46,310 --> 00:16:50,000
Because I like seeing your instant reaction when I make fun of you.

215
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:53,490
Fine. I guess you want to hurry up and see the camera.

216
00:16:53,490 --> 00:16:58,910
Do you think I want to see the camera or you more?

217
00:16:59,990 --> 00:17:02,720
- Where are you?
- At work.

218
00:17:02,720 --> 00:17:04,430
Still?

219
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:08,050
I guess you're working overtime.

220
00:17:08,730 --> 00:17:11,670
I guess the CEO should go there to cheer you on.

221
00:17:11,670 --> 00:17:14,330
Then I guess I'll wait here.

222
00:17:14,330 --> 00:17:16,620
Grilled beef small intestines

223
00:17:23,430 --> 00:17:26,500
It's cooked well.

224
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,650
Try it with the sauce.

225
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:38,320
There are over a million things I like after having met you,

226
00:17:38,320 --> 00:17:40,560
and one of those things is a mysterious experience.

227
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:41,790
Mysterious?

228
00:17:41,790 --> 00:17:45,490
Chicken feet, chicken gizzard, beef tripe, they're all mysterious to me.

229
00:17:45,490 --> 00:17:50,230
They're mysterious, but once you eat them... how should I put it, they feel familiar, right?

230
00:17:50,230 --> 00:17:52,870
There's one thing you need to know.

231
00:17:52,870 --> 00:17:55,610
I'm normally a very picky eater.

232
00:17:55,610 --> 00:18:00,060
But whatever you ask to eat, I never say I can't, and I eat everything well.

233
00:18:00,060 --> 00:18:03,340
Acknowledged. You're the best, seriously.

234
00:18:04,980 --> 00:18:07,530
Here. Eat a lot.

235
00:18:09,020 --> 00:18:10,890
Now, let's have a look.

236
00:18:10,890 --> 00:18:13,530
There's no second half when it comes to tripe?

237
00:18:13,530 --> 00:18:15,070
Really? You can keep going?

238
00:18:15,070 --> 00:18:17,620
This is my first meal today.

239
00:18:17,620 --> 00:18:19,810
- Excuse me, please mix the rice for us!
- Yes.

240
00:18:19,810 --> 00:18:22,800
That's right. Fried rice is a perfect second half.

241
00:18:22,800 --> 00:18:26,770
Come on, show it to me once before we eat fried rice.

242
00:18:27,830 --> 00:18:30,550
We can't get any oil on it, though.

243
00:18:41,050 --> 00:18:43,620
Wow, it's amazing.

244
00:18:43,620 --> 00:18:47,330
It's the same model, so it's obviously going to look exactly the same,

245
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:50,520
but it's so strange.

246
00:18:51,230 --> 00:18:53,540
Maybe because it's something that captures your emotions?

247
