00:40:50,350 --> 00:40:54,520
It's D-Day. How will the votes regarding CEO Cha's reappointment turn out?

497
00:40:54,520 --> 00:40:56,350
Isn't it corrupt if we know beforehand?

498
00:40:56,350 --> 00:40:58,580
There's something called "predictable".

499
00:40:58,600 --> 00:41:01,770
There are several directors who are already congratulating you before the voting.

500
00:41:01,770 --> 00:41:03,650
I want to see a list of those directors.

501
00:41:03,650 --> 00:41:07,070
Won't you see them at the celebration anyway?

502
00:41:09,010 --> 00:41:12,670
Thank you for taking time to attend this meeting despite your busy schedules.

503
00:41:12,670 --> 00:41:16,100
In order to carry out the voting regarding CEO Cha Soo Hyeon's reappointment,

504
00:41:16,100 --> 00:41:18,890
I will give you a few...

505
00:41:28,520 --> 00:41:32,430
Before you do that, there is an important matter that needs to be addressed.

506
00:41:32,430 --> 00:41:35,680
Let's handle other matters after the voting.

507
00:41:35,680 --> 00:41:38,780
It won't take long.

508
00:41:45,290 --> 00:41:47,320
Come in.

509
00:42:10,390 --> 00:42:15,060
First, I extend my apologies.

510
00:42:16,450 --> 00:42:22,230
I was blinded for a moment and made a huge mistake.

511
00:42:26,240 --> 00:42:32,670
I persuaded Manager Kim to cause the incident with the email for Cuba Hotel.

512
00:42:32,700 --> 00:42:38,000
I told him to send an email that could cancel Cuba Hotel's construction and then resign.

513
00:42:38,030 --> 00:42:41,190
- Wait, what is this?
- What is he saying?

514
00:42:41,220 --> 00:42:43,950
Why did you do that?

515
00:42:54,180 --> 00:42:57,040
It was under Director Choi Jin Cheul's orders.

516
00:42:57,040 --> 00:43:00,510
- What?
- What did he say?
- That can't be. Director Choi?

517
00:43:06,850 --> 00:43:09,890
Accordingly,

518
00:43:12,270 --> 00:43:15,990
I demand an apology from Director Choi Jin Cheul.

519
00:43:15,990 --> 00:43:19,790
If you really admit your fault and apologize sincerely,

520
00:43:19,790 --> 00:43:23,370
then this issue will end here.

521
00:43:23,400 --> 00:43:26,600
I think that this is slander against me, CEO Cha.

522
00:43:26,600 --> 00:43:28,140
I'm giving you a chance.

523
00:43:28,200 --> 00:43:30,900
If I'm the one who gave Section Chief Lee the orders,

524
00:43:30,900 --> 00:43:33,700
then who do you think gave those orders to me?

525
00:43:33,700 --> 00:43:39,500
Is it that difficult to say a single word of a sincere apology?

526
00:43:41,540 --> 00:43:46,900
I was just a hired hand.

527
00:43:50,880 --> 00:43:53,850
Who were you hired by?

528
00:44:02,080 --> 00:44:06,450
I will follow the decision of CEO Jeong Woo Seok, Director Choi Jin Cheul,

529
00:44:06,450 --> 00:44:09,320
and several other directors here.

530
00:44:09,320 --> 00:44:13,820
I hope that you will also relay the results of the remaining issues to me as well.

531
00:44:27,820 --> 00:44:33,870
This happened before I was appointed to this position, so the directors should handle this matter.

532
00:44:36,250 --> 00:44:41,240
I think that it would be best to hold the meeting regarding her reappointment at another time.

533
00:44:54,600 --> 00:44:57,350
Even though they tried to cover it up, I think the rumors have all spread by now.

534
00:44:57,350 --> 00:45:00,650
What will Section Chief Lee do now?

535
00:45:00,650 --> 00:45:03,470
He looked really haggard when I saw him this morning.

536
00:45:03,470 --> 00:45:06,170
He's probably having a hard time himself.

537
00:45:06,210 --> 00:45:08,380
The CEO is amazing.

538
00:45:08,380 --> 00:45:10,640
I would have fired him right away if it were me.

539
00:45:10,640 --> 00:45:13,060
How could she think of sending him to Cuba to be a team leader?

540
00:45:13,990 --> 00:45:17,750
Someone committed a great wrong toward me.

541
00:45:17,750 --> 00:45:20,740
Let's say that I suffered a lot because of that.

542
00:45:20,780 --> 00:45:23,610
But then I found out who that person is.

543
00:45:23,610 --> 00:45:25,620
What should I do?

544
00:45:27,740 --> 00:45:30,240
What do you think will happen to Section Chief Lee?

545
00:45:30,960 --> 00:45:33,040
I don't know.

546
00:45:33,040 --> 00:45:34,890
Let's go back.

547
00:45:53,290 --> 00:45:57,240
I thought I'd be here longer than you at least.

548
00:45:57,240 --> 00:46:01,210
But you never know about life. It's amusing.

549
00:46:01,850 --> 00:46:06,690
Don't feel relieved that this war is over just because I'm leaving.

550
00:46:13,650 --> 00:46:15,970
He's unlikable to the very end.

551
00:46:15,970 --> 00:46:17,710
Let's go.

552
00:46:33,420 --> 00:46:35,810
Can I see you briefly?

553
00:46:40,870 --> 00:46:43,130
Can you set aside some time tonight?

554
00:46:43,130 --> 00:46:46,800
Why are you so sure that I don't have my own plans tonight?

555
00:46:46,800 --> 00:46:47,950
Do you?

556
00:46:47,950 --> 00:46:50,490
I don't. Why?

557
00:46:50,490 --> 00:46:51,510
Let's eat.

558
00:46:51,510 --> 00:46:52,970
Ah, where?

559
00:46:52,970 --> 00:46:54,200
At my home.

560
00:46:54,200 --> 00:46:57,800
Okay, then what do you want me to bring over as our menu?

561
00:46:57,800 --> 00:47:01,880
Just come over. I'm thinking about making something tonight.

562
00:47:01,880 --> 00:47:02,480
What?

563
00:47:02,480 --> 00:47:04,250
Ask Manager Nam to come, too.

564
00:47:04,250 --> 00:47:08,470
You both worked hard on the Choi case, so I should give you my thanks.

565
00:47:08,470 --> 00:47:10,610
Let's just eat out.

566
00:47:10,610 --> 00:47:13,330
Come around 8.

567
00:47:13,330 --> 00:47:17,720
I was worried since I haven't seen you around much, so I came over.

568
00:47:17,720 --> 00:47:21,830
You like zucchini pancakes.

569
00:47:21,830 --> 00:47:25,430
It looks good. I was hungry.

570
00:47:25,430 --> 00:47:28,190
Thank you. I'll enjoy it.

571
00:47:29,410 --> 00:47:31,400
You made it so well.

572
00:47:31,400 --> 00:47:35,040
I can't make it crispy like this.

573
00:47:36,650 --> 00:47:40,250
Excuse me, Jin Hyeok's mom.

574
00:47:53,670 --> 00:47:57,010
Please get my son a job at that hotel.

575
00:47:57,010 --> 00:47:59,490
I'm begging you like this.

576
00:47:59,490 --> 00:48:05,160
Wait. Why would you ask such a thing of me?

577
00:48:05,160 --> 00:48:09,630
To be honest, since he has a relationship with the CEO,

578
00:48:09,630 --> 00:48:12,660
it must have been easy for him to get a job there.

579
00:48:14,400 --> 00:48:19,610
Then where do I have to call to get in touch with the CEO?

580
00:48:19,610 --> 00:48:21,470
I'm sorry, customer.

581
00:48:21,470 --> 00:48:27,720
We are not able to put you through since we are not in charge of the CEO's office.

582
00:48:27,720 --> 00:48:30,260
Do you have any other questions?

583
00:48:30,260 --> 00:48:33,700
No. It's all right.

584
00:48:52,240 --> 00:48:56,290
You're really a good cook. It's unexpected.

585
00:48:56,290 --> 00:49:00,150
Leave it, and go and get some rest. It was a lot of work, right?

586
00:49:00,150 --> 00:49:04,470
All I did was hand you the ingredients. You had a harder time.

587
00:49:04,470 --> 00:49:06,810
Still.

588
00:49:06,810 --> 00:49:11,700
Cooking and setting the table together like this,

589
00:49:11,700 --> 00:49:13,980
it feels really special.

590
00:49:17,010 --> 00:49:21,480
You cook well, too, and just too perfect.

591
00:49:21,480 --> 00:49:24,140
When did you learn all this?

592
00:49:26,490 --> 00:49:28,580
They should be here by now.

593
00:49:28,580 --> 00:49:30,480
I'll call—

594
00:49:44,870 --> 00:49:48,250
Thank you, Ahjussi. I took care of it well thanks to you.

595
00:49:48,250 --> 00:49:51,500
I didn't do anything. I did well, though. Right?

596
00:49:51,500 --> 00:49:52,910
Yes, thank you.

597
00:49:52,910 --> 00:49:55,230
I acknowledge that you used to be a reporter.

598
00:49:55,230 --> 00:49:57,060
I told you so many times and now you acknowledge it?

599
00:49:57,060 --> 00:50:00,510
I'm the suspicious type.

600
00:50:01,750 --> 00:50:03,570
Did you cook, too?

601
00:50:03,570 --> 00:50:05,310
I just prepared the ingredients.

602
00:50:05,310 --> 00:50:07,680
That takes more work.

603
00:50:07,680 --> 00:50:12,550
That's the way it naturally is! Even if there is no salty food at the restaurant, you just peel the onions. While crying!

604
00:50:12,550 --> 00:50:15,500
I guess this is the time for caring about each other. You worked hard, CEO.

605
00:50:15,500 --> 00:50:19,370
Jin Hyeok, you had more work to do, right? I told you we should eat out!

606
00:50:19,370 --> 00:50:21,090
It's my wish. You can't just go along with it?

607
00:50:21,090 --> 00:50:24,490
What wish? This is your wish? Eating soybean paste stew? Rice and side dishes?

608
00:50:24,490 --> 00:50:26,080
To me, it's more like a Korean Table d'hôte.
(a menu with only a few choices charged at a fixed total price)

609
00:50:26,080 --> 00:50:28,410
I see. I hope you two live and eat well together.

610
00:50:28,410 --> 00:50:29,430
Stop picking on them.

611
00:50:29,430 --> 00:50:31,590
If you're jealous, get married.

612
00:50:31,590 --> 00:50:33,120
Ah, let's eat.

613
00:50:33,120 --> 00:50:35,280
Thank you for the meal.

614
00:50:37,850 --> 00:50:39,480
Where to start...

615
00:50:43,060 --> 00:50:45,280
It's good, huh?

616
00:50:45,280 --> 00:50:48,310
But isn't the wish a little too small, Ahjussi?

617
00:50:48,310 --> 00:50:50,890
It's not small.

618
00:50:50,890 --> 00:50:53,250
To me, this is hard.

619
00:50:53,250 --> 00:50:56,200
The food or us?

620
00:50:56,200 --> 00:51:00,850
Eating a meal that I prepared and eating with those I care about.

621
00:51:00,850 --> 00:51:02,680
To me, it was difficult.

622
00:51:02,680 --> 00:51:05,490
So it can be my wish.

623
00:51:13,490 --> 00:51:15,600
I was honestly a little hurt.

624
00:51:15,600 --> 00:51:16,970
Why? About what?

625
00:51:16,970 --> 00:51:20,070
This is the first time I've been here after the day she moved in.

626
00:51:20,070 --> 00:51:22,700
It's not like she moved in a few days ago. It's been years.

627
00:51:22,700 --> 00:51:26,700
And then saying, "You want to come eat?" Would you feel hurt or not?

628
00:51:26,700 --> 00:51:30,220
I don't think I'd feel that hurt.

629
00:51:30,220 --> 00:51:33,550
Asking him is 100% loss for you. You should have asked me instead.

630
00:51:33,550 --> 00:51:36,080
Of course, you would be hurt. I should have invited you sooner.

631
00:51:36,080 --> 00:51:38,890
Enjoy the food today and forgive me.

632
00:51:38,890 --> 00:51:43,210
Well, I thought this day would never come. I'm happy.

633
00:51:43,210 --> 00:51:46,190
You're changing too fast. Take your time.

634
00:51:46,190 --> 00:51:49,630
Do you think she's changing? She's coming back to herself.

635
00:51:49,630 --> 00:51:53,950
Don't call me over with Ahjussi. He nags way too much.

636
00:51:53,950 --> 00:51:57,040
But don't you think you're too dressed down?

637
00:51:57,040 --> 00:52:02,290
Since we're eating a home-cooked meal, shouldn't I dress down like this?

638
00:52:02,290 --> 00:52:04,560
Give me a change of clothes so I can eat comfortably.

639
00:52:04,560 --> 00:52:06,230
I'll give it to you. Eat first.

640
00:52:06,230 --> 00:52:07,450
Then don't you have something for Ahjussi?

641
00:52:07,450 --> 00:52:10,650
Do you think I'd be comfortable if I wore Soo Hyeon's clothes?

642
00:52:12,890 --> 00:52:14,340
I'd like that.

643
00:52:25,370 --> 00:52:28,330
Are you sure that she can't come because of work?

644
00:52:28,330 --> 00:52:33,220
Dae Chan asked Secretary Jang to work in my place.

645
00:52:37,230 --> 00:52:39,330
We can't tell yet.
(T.N.: Dad is watching a Baduk ("Go") match on television)

646
00:52:42,260 --> 00:52:45,590
He does have to counter here.

647
00:52:45,590 --> 00:52:50,030
But he chose to place his stone adjacent instead which means that he is choosing the two remaining spaces.

648
00:52:50,030 --> 00:52:51,820
I see that, too.

649
00:52:51,820 --> 00:52:58,250
Park Jeong Hwan is a professional baduk player representing our country.

650
00:52:58,250 --> 00:53:00,920
He has studied immensely.

651
00:53:00,920 --> 00:53:05,180
He has already studied most of patterns and has them under his belt.

652
00:53:05,180 --> 00:53:10,790
Most players would panic under unexpected patterns like this.

653
00:53:10,820 --> 00:53:12,770
Are you going somewhere?

654
00:53:12,770 --> 00:53:14,280
Next door.

655
00:53:14,280 --> 00:53:17,290
The tangerine syrup tastes good.

656
00:53:23,010 --> 00:53:24,230
Come in, it's cold.
Chan's Whelks

657
00:53:24,230 --> 00:53:28,870
It's all right. I have to leave soon.

658
00:53:28,870 --> 00:53:30,710
Excuse me, Dae Chan.

659
00:53:30,710 --> 00:53:32,730
Yes.

660
00:53:32,730 --> 00:53:38,700
Could you give this to that secretary person?

661
00:53:38,700 --> 00:53:40,080
- Secretary Jang?
- Yes.

662
00:53:40,080 --> 00:53:42,300
What is it?

663
00:53:43,210 --> 00:53:46,320
Ask her to give this to the CEO.

664
00:53:46,320 --> 00:53:47,610
CEO?

665
00:53:47,610 --> 00:53:49,870
Yes.

666
00:53:49,900 --> 00:53:57,100
And please don't tell Jin Hyeok and Jin Myeong about this.

667
00:53:57,100 --> 00:53:59,800
All right, I won't.

668
00:53:59,800 --> 00:54:01,200
Go on in. It's cold.

669
00:54:01,210 --> 00:54:02,770
Yes.

670
00:54:02,770 --> 00:54:06,710
Chan's Whelks

671
00:54:18,370 --> 00:54:19,810
Give me. I'll do it.

672
00:54:19,810 --> 00:54:22,010
I did it all already.

673
00:54:29,930 --> 00:54:34,250
So many things happened today. I'm tired.

674
00:54:44,760 --> 00:54:49,830
This feels like my place, too. The whole house feels comfortable.

675
00:54:49,830 --> 00:54:54,230
I thought your room looked comfortable. It looked cozy.

676
00:54:54,230 --> 00:54:55,580
That's a good place, too.

677
00:54:55,580 --> 00:54:58,640
It's small, so you have to stick together.

678
00:54:58,640 --> 00:55:02,150
It doesn't feel like we're apart now.

679
00:55:07,150 --> 00:55:12,480
You know that I'm very busy keeping my 10 centimeter distance from you, right?

680
00:55:12,480 --> 00:55:14,220
I know.

681
00:55:14,220 --> 00:55:18,210
You came early today and helped out a lot.

682
00:55:18,210 --> 00:55:21,010
You're so reliable.

683
00:55:21,010 --> 00:55:26,730
You say I'm reliable, but why aren't you giving me an answer?

684
00:55:26,730 --> 00:55:28,920
What?

685
00:55:28,920 --> 00:55:34,910
I asked you to live together with me for a long, long time.

686
00:55:36,680 --> 00:55:38,990
But you avoided answering me.

687
00:56:01,970 --> 00:56:07,010
♫ You can't start entering ♫

688
00:56:07,010 --> 00:56:11,280
I'm very good at cooking Italian food.

689
00:56:11,280 --> 00:56:14,640
You see? You're avoiding it again.

690
00:56:14,640 --> 00:56:16,920
I can cook Chinese food, too.

691
00:56:16,920 --> 00:56:18,990
I cook Japanese food some, too.

692
00:56:18,990 --> 00:56:24,560
♫ Your sparkling eyes shine ♫

693
00:56:24,560 --> 00:56:26,490
After I went to live in Taegyeong,

694
00:56:26,490 --> 00:56:28,460
♫ and shake my heart ♫

695
00:56:28,460 --> 00:56:31,820
I learned it all.

696
00:56:31,820 --> 00:56:38,590
♫ The more I like you ♫

697
00:56:38,590 --> 00:56:42,570
♫  The more I depend on you ♫

698
00:56:43,650 --> 00:56:46,230
So what?

699
00:56:46,230 --> 00:56:49,120
It's good that you can cook.

700
00:56:49,120 --> 00:56:51,040
♫ The heart that is unwilling to depart ♫

701
00:56:51,040 --> 00:56:55,520
Jin Hyeok.

702
00:56:55,520 --> 00:57:00,510
After I went to your house,

703
00:57:00,510 --> 00:57:03,230
I keep having dreams.

704
00:57:03,230 --> 00:57:08,900
I want to be happy together in that house, too.

705
00:57:11,240 --> 00:57:13,900
That will happen.

706
00:57:17,470 --> 00:57:20,530
I keep getting held back

707
00:57:20,530 --> 00:57:25,310
by my memories and my past.

708
00:57:28,680 --> 00:57:35,180
I want to hold a pretty bouquet like that

709
00:57:35,180 --> 00:57:37,560
and stand in front of you, too.

710
00:57:37,560 --> 00:57:43,200
But... I'm not sure

711
00:57:43,200 --> 00:57:45,760
if that's really something I'm allowed to dream about.

712
00:57:45,760 --> 00:57:49,540
♫ My feelings won't stop ♫

713
00:57:49,540 --> 00:57:53,380
I feel like I'm being too greedy,

714
00:57:53,380 --> 00:57:57,630
so I'm kind of sad.
♫ My heart will never ever ♫

715
00:57:57,630 --> 00:58:01,920
♫ go to you ♫

716
00:58:24,350 --> 00:58:29,520
I met a woman in Cuba,

717
00:58:29,520 --> 00:58:34,450
and I didn't even know her name or what kind of person she was.

718
00:58:34,450 --> 00:58:39,810
But the day that I first met her,

719
00:58:41,470 --> 00:58:46,310
I thought, "Does this woman possibly have a boyfriend?"

720
00:58:48,520 --> 00:58:51,070
"I hope she doesn't have one."

721
00:58:55,730 --> 00:59:02,500
Cha Soo Hyeon, you're the woman from that day.

722
00:59:05,140 --> 00:59:11,610
You're the first person to enter deeply into my heart.

723
00:59:16,800 --> 00:59:21,620
Your past isn't that important to me.

724
00:59:21,620 --> 00:59:24,550
♫  I can't hide anywhere ♫

725
00:59:24,550 --> 00:59:27,500
Because I love one person, Cha Soo Hyeon.

726
00:59:27,500 --> 00:59:30,720
♫  Is this what they have been calling love? ♫

727
00:59:30,720 --> 00:59:33,560
With that one person,

728
00:59:33,560 --> 00:59:40,740
I want to be together every single day.
♫ And it just goes on Oh take me on to you ♫

729
00:59:40,740 --> 00:59:43,510
I look forward to it every day.

730
00:59:45,280 --> 00:59:50,430
♫  You're my flower and I'm your bee ♫

731
00:59:50,430 --> 00:59:53,360
♫  You know you keep me alive ♫

732
00:59:53,360 --> 00:59:56,790
Can we do that?

733
00:59:56,790 --> 00:59:58,530
♫  You’re my reasons for everything I do  ♫

734
00:59:58,530 --> 01:00:01,870
You're going to let us do that, right?

735
01:00:01,870 --> 01:00:03,290
♫  The other half of me ♫

736
01:00:03,290 --> 01:00:07,310
I will do that.

737
01:00:07,310 --> 01:00:13,990
♫ Oh take me on down on a river  ♫

738
01:00:13,990 --> 01:00:18,590
♫  I'll go wherever it leads to you ♫

739
01:00:18,590 --> 01:00:25,270
♫  Oh take me on into your arms ♫

740
01:00:25,270 --> 01:00:30,120
♫  I'll go wherever world you’re on ♫

741
01:00:58,010 --> 01:01:01,350
Please preserve these flowers.

742
01:01:01,350 --> 01:01:04,020
Preserve? What is that?

743
01:01:04,020 --> 01:01:08,750
I heard that you could treat them with a special solution so that they won't wither.

744
01:01:08,750 --> 01:01:10,360
Oh, I think I've heard of that.

745
01:01:10,360 --> 01:01:12,040
Give it to me.

746
01:01:13,020 --> 01:01:15,100
What is it?

747
01:01:15,100 --> 01:01:20,590
Kim Jin Hyeok's mother told me to give this to you.

748
01:01:20,590 --> 01:01:25,560
I didn't get it from her personally. The boss of Chan's Whelks gave it to me.

749
01:01:25,560 --> 01:01:27,190
Yes.

750
01:01:48,800 --> 01:01:51,990
I'm sorry for contacting you so suddenly.

751
01:01:51,990 --> 01:01:54,710
I was wondering if there was a way that we could meet with each other.

752
01:01:54,710 --> 01:01:57,600
Please call me at this phone number.

753
01:01:57,600 --> 01:02:01,080
You must be busy. I'm sorry.

754
01:02:23,550 --> 01:02:28,090
You were really surprised that I got in touch with you suddenly, weren't you?

755
01:02:28,090 --> 01:02:31,930
No. I enjoyed the tangerine syrup that you sent me.

756
01:02:31,930 --> 01:02:33,660
Thank you.

757
01:02:33,660 --> 01:02:35,330
Yes.

758
01:03:02,360 --> 01:03:09,260
Um... I'm not good at beating around the bush.

759
01:03:09,260 --> 01:03:12,150
Please speak comfortably.

760
01:03:14,240 --> 01:03:20,380
CEO, I am sorry.

761
01:03:21,160 --> 01:03:23,160
Sorry.

762
01:03:25,870 --> 01:03:32,990
Please break up with our Jin Hyeok.

763
01:03:37,020 --> 01:03:41,120
Our next door neighbor came to me.

764
01:03:41,120 --> 01:03:45,830
She asked me to get her son hired at Donghwa Hotel.

765
01:03:45,830 --> 01:03:50,300
I sent her away because it was such an absurd request,

766
01:03:50,960 --> 01:03:54,480
but all of my neighbors are saying this.

767
01:03:54,480 --> 01:04:00,620
They're saying that he didn't make it into the company normally.

768
01:04:00,620 --> 01:04:06,880
That it's because he's with you that he got into the company.

769
01:04:06,880 --> 01:04:11,590
But my Jin Hyeok didn't get into the company like that. Right?

770
01:04:15,830 --> 01:04:22,150
I've ended up having to live my life explaining something that's so obviously true.

771
01:04:30,780 --> 01:04:36,870
CEO. You're really upset too, aren't you?

772
01:04:37,770 --> 01:04:44,410
I want my family to continue living quietly

773
01:04:44,410 --> 01:04:48,450
and happily, as we are now.

774
01:04:48,450 --> 01:04:52,880
If someone in such a high station as you is with our Jin Hyeok...

775
01:04:56,740 --> 01:05:01,250
And you aren't going to marry our Jin Hyeok, right?

776
01:05:04,000 --> 01:05:07,670
People don't all get married just because they've dated.

777
01:05:08,500 --> 01:05:11,390
But, CEO.

778
01:05:11,390 --> 01:05:17,910
You and our Jin Hyeok are very different.

779
01:05:23,180 --> 01:05:26,100
Because I'm so lacking,

780
01:05:27,010 --> 01:05:32,490
I'm anxious and my insides are being burned to a crisp.

781
01:05:33,930 --> 01:05:38,860
I'm worried that my child will just get hurt if this continues.

782
01:05:38,860 --> 01:05:43,000
I'm worried that he'll be talked about by people for a long time.

783
01:05:43,000 --> 01:05:47,970
I'm scared to death.

784
01:05:51,100 --> 01:05:56,130
CEO. I'm sorry.

785
01:05:56,130 --> 01:05:58,420
I'm really sorry.

786
01:05:59,270 --> 01:06:02,510
Please, please, with our Jin Hyeok...

787
01:06:02,510 --> 01:06:06,330
Please break up with our Jin Hyeok.

788
01:06:37,090 --> 01:06:44,450
♫ When the door opens, you whom I love come to me ♫

789
01:06:44,450 --> 01:06:50,430
I can't even imagine my days without you now.

790
01:06:50,430 --> 01:06:55,500
Live together with me for a long, long time.

791
01:06:55,500 --> 01:06:59,870
I love you, Cha Soo Hyeon.

792
01:07:01,120 --> 01:07:04,950
♫  A fairy tale where I dance holding you ♫

793
01:07:04,950 --> 01:07:12,070
♫ While I spend such a day with you ♫

794
01:07:12,070 --> 01:07:19,610
♫ I don't want to wake up from that fairytale-like dream ♫

795
01:07:20,860 --> 01:07:30,450
♫ I don't want to wake up and leave from here ♫

796
01:07:30,500 --> 01:07:38,250
♫ I want to dream and hold you a little longer ♫

797
01:07:38,250 --> 01:07:44,670
♫ It seems if I wake up these many stories ♫

798
01:07:44,670 --> 01:07:48,920
♫ will all disappear.  ♫

799
01:07:48,920 --> 01:07:53,760
Encounter Preview 
♫  While I'm thinking that.  ♫

800
01:07:53,760 --> 01:07:56,210
I treasure the CEO greatly.

801
01:07:56,210 --> 01:08:00,840
How long will this flower last without withering?

802
01:08:00,850 --> 01:08:03,750
Why? I'm just saying it because I'm envious.

803
01:08:03,750 --> 01:08:07,550
It didn't happen because of you, so don't misunderstand.

804
01:08:07,550 --> 01:08:12,910
If the ordinary happiness of Jin Hyeok's family is shaken because of me,

805
01:08:12,910 --> 01:08:15,240
there's no answer for that.

806
01:08:15,240 --> 01:08:17,530
I learned this thanks to you, Woo Seok.

807
01:08:17,530 --> 01:08:18,390
Jin Hyeok

808
01:08:18,390 --> 01:08:21,170
How I should break up with someone.
